President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Vermont and ordered Federal assistance to supplement State and local recovery efforts following severe storms and flooding that occurred from May 4 to May 5, 2018. The declaration makes federal funding available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The affected counties include Chittenden, Grand Isle, Lamoille, Orange, and Orleans. Additionally, federal funding is available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on requested assessments of damage. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.